WEBVTT

00:00:00.207 --> 00:00:01.552
- Can I touch it?

00:00:01.552 --> 00:00:04.800
[mellow music]
[car horns honking]

00:00:04.800 --> 00:00:08.613
Hi, I'm Lisa and this is my
final fitting for the Met Gala.

00:00:16.538 --> 00:00:18.340
[Lisa giggles]

00:00:18.340 --> 00:00:20.508
[Lisa gasps]

00:00:20.508 --> 00:00:23.569
[chuckles] Oh, my God.

00:00:23.569 --> 00:00:25.986
[Lisa gasps]

00:00:27.480 --> 00:00:28.399
Hello, by the way.

00:00:28.399 --> 00:00:30.090
[both laughing]

00:00:30.090 --> 00:00:33.270
Meeting him for the first
time, he's like warm-hearted.

00:00:33.270 --> 00:00:35.647
I feel like I know him such a long time.

00:00:35.647 --> 00:00:37.470
- The first time she wore my pieces

00:00:37.470 --> 00:00:39.900
was maybe a good five, six years ago.

00:00:39.900 --> 00:00:42.000
After all these years,
we've been dressing her.

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:45.600
This feels very full circle,
and yeah, she's incredible.

00:00:45.600 --> 00:00:48.210
- What's the first thing
that popped into my head

00:00:48.210 --> 00:00:50.310
when I first saw the look?

00:00:50.310 --> 00:00:51.270
It's incredible.

00:00:51.270 --> 00:00:52.350
It's art.

00:00:52.350 --> 00:00:56.850
But it's my hands, my arms. [laughs]

00:00:56.850 --> 00:00:57.990
- The theme for Met this year

00:00:57.990 --> 00:01:00.150
is around this big picture of art.

00:01:00.150 --> 00:01:01.530
And I think so many people are going

00:01:01.530 --> 00:01:04.620
to do what their
rendition of the theme is,

00:01:04.620 --> 00:01:07.260
but Robert is like the epitome of art,

00:01:07.260 --> 00:01:09.690
and construction, and the female body.

00:01:09.690 --> 00:01:13.110
I knew he was the guy
that we should go with.

00:01:13.110 --> 00:01:14.610
- [Robert] Get it on the shoulder.

00:01:14.610 --> 00:01:15.443
There you go.

00:01:15.443 --> 00:01:16.320
You can feel...

00:01:16.320 --> 00:01:18.014
How does it feel? [chuckles]

00:01:18.014 --> 00:01:18.972
- [Lisa] Okay.

00:01:18.972 --> 00:01:19.805
Okay.
- Yeah, okay, okay.

00:01:19.805 --> 00:01:21.079
- Okay.
[Robert laughs]

00:01:21.079 --> 00:01:21.912
- All right.
[Lisa laughs]

00:01:21.912 --> 00:01:23.010
- Is it heavy?

00:01:23.010 --> 00:01:25.650
So we had a 3D scan done of Lisa's body.

00:01:25.650 --> 00:01:27.120
And the really special thing,

00:01:27.120 --> 00:01:29.100
how Robert manipulated the arms,

00:01:29.100 --> 00:01:32.340
it feels very poetic
to her Thai background

00:01:32.340 --> 00:01:34.890
and the Thai dance moves that they will do

00:01:34.890 --> 00:01:37.890
and just this like
beautiful poetry of fashion

00:01:37.890 --> 00:01:40.770
and choreography that is just so Lisa.

00:01:40.770 --> 00:01:42.060
That makes it even more special.

00:01:42.060 --> 00:01:43.980
'Cause sometimes these girls
will just put on a piece of art

00:01:43.980 --> 00:01:45.090
to put on a piece of art, right?

00:01:45.090 --> 00:01:48.180
But this, at the core, feels like her.

00:01:48.180 --> 00:01:50.720
Her love for where she's
from, Thailand, is just like,

00:01:50.720 --> 00:01:53.070
it makes it so perfect.

00:01:53.070 --> 00:01:54.360
- I am nervous for tomorrow

00:01:54.360 --> 00:01:58.170
because my extra arms is
really heavy. [laughs]

00:01:58.170 --> 00:02:01.320
He said it's 1.8 kilo,
but I don't think so.

00:02:01.320 --> 00:02:02.880
I think it's heavier than that.

00:02:02.880 --> 00:02:04.500
But I have to fight through it

00:02:04.500 --> 00:02:06.690
'cause the concept is Costume Art,

00:02:06.690 --> 00:02:11.220
so it's really nice to have
me as an art on the carpet.

00:02:11.220 --> 00:02:13.170
Yeah, I'm just so excited to see everyone

00:02:13.170 --> 00:02:14.850
'cause it's my second Met.

00:02:14.850 --> 00:02:16.230
- For me, I'm a maximalist.

00:02:16.230 --> 00:02:18.720
I really love a lot of things

00:02:18.720 --> 00:02:21.570
to just make it feel like
a treasure box kind of.

00:02:21.570 --> 00:02:24.360
But on Lisa, we've kept it
a little bit more delicate.

00:02:24.360 --> 00:02:26.460
There's obviously the
big sapphire necklace

00:02:26.460 --> 00:02:27.660
that we both love,

00:02:27.660 --> 00:02:30.270
but on the arms, that's
where the more is more is.

00:02:30.270 --> 00:02:32.940
I think her we're keeping
a little bit more subtle

00:02:32.940 --> 00:02:35.100
because it's about the
look and her beauty,

00:02:35.100 --> 00:02:36.720
but with the secondary part of arms,

00:02:36.720 --> 00:02:39.150
it's like stack the shit
out of this Bulgari.

00:02:39.150 --> 00:02:42.900
And it just makes it feel
even more special and iconic.

00:02:42.900 --> 00:02:44.310
- It's already heavy,

00:02:44.310 --> 00:02:45.143
so you know-
- I'm like,

00:02:45.143 --> 00:02:46.487
are you gaslighting me now?
- Adding a little more

00:02:46.487 --> 00:02:47.320
is fine.
[Brett laughs]

00:02:47.320 --> 00:02:48.570
- [Attendant] What's another 30 carats?

00:02:48.570 --> 00:02:49.920
Just-
- Yeah.

00:02:49.920 --> 00:02:52.440
- I have this amazing glassblower.

00:02:52.440 --> 00:02:55.020
I wanted to do a bag that looked like ice.

00:02:55.020 --> 00:02:57.180
I grew up in Missouri in
like a really small town,

00:02:57.180 --> 00:02:58.500
so when winters came,

00:02:58.500 --> 00:03:02.220
the ice would just drip down
our house and it's so cool.

00:03:02.220 --> 00:03:04.410
It's stuff like this that
just are like little cherries

00:03:04.410 --> 00:03:06.645
on top of already perfect couture.

00:03:06.645 --> 00:03:07.860
[mellow music]

00:03:07.860 --> 00:03:09.870
- The most exciting for tomorrow?

00:03:09.870 --> 00:03:11.683
Uh, [laughs]

00:03:13.290 --> 00:03:14.760
I don't know, it's just the red carpet.

00:03:14.760 --> 00:03:16.890
I really want to make it work.

00:03:16.890 --> 00:03:19.094
I'm scared to you know?

00:03:19.094 --> 00:03:22.170
[chuckles] Yeah, I don't
wanna trip tomorrow, so.

00:03:22.170 --> 00:03:23.850
- Let's grab both sides,

00:03:23.850 --> 00:03:25.491
the underskirt.
- And then you take

00:03:25.491 --> 00:03:27.032
a few step back, right?
- Do you want me

00:03:27.032 --> 00:03:28.860
to try to walk?
- So yeah, let's go, let's go.

00:03:28.860 --> 00:03:30.360
- Yeah, just give it a
walk and see how she feels.

00:03:30.360 --> 00:03:31.305
- [Lisa] Oh, my god.

00:03:31.305 --> 00:03:32.850
I'm doing a practice right now?

00:03:32.850 --> 00:03:33.792
- Okay, let's put the veil-
- Yeah.

00:03:33.792 --> 00:03:35.370
- [Brett] Back on.

00:03:35.370 --> 00:03:36.338
- Working out.

00:03:36.338 --> 00:03:37.171
[Brett laughs]

00:03:37.171 --> 00:03:38.340
It's heavy, guys.

00:03:38.340 --> 00:03:39.173
- Yeah.
- With help-

00:03:39.173 --> 00:03:41.730
- [Lisa] Maybe I need a different shoes.

00:03:41.730 --> 00:03:42.690
- [Brett] Which if this is the case,

00:03:42.690 --> 00:03:44.310
we might need to look
at shortening it a bit

00:03:44.310 --> 00:03:45.960
'cause they are shortening.
- No, I feel like the heels

00:03:45.960 --> 00:03:48.810
is not gonna help me balance it.

00:03:48.810 --> 00:03:49.740
- [Brett] These?

00:03:49.740 --> 00:03:50.700
- No, the thin.

00:03:50.700 --> 00:03:52.110
I need the thicker.

00:03:52.110 --> 00:03:54.060
- [Brett] Maybe if you're
feeling good with the top part,

00:03:54.060 --> 00:03:55.440
let's take the arms off.

00:03:55.440 --> 00:03:56.273
- Yes.

00:03:56.273 --> 00:03:57.106
- And let's take them down.
[Robert laughs]

00:03:57.106 --> 00:03:58.487
- Take them, please.

00:03:59.400 --> 00:04:00.570
- We'll try these just to see,

00:04:00.570 --> 00:04:02.670
and then we'll work on
thickening out a heel.

00:04:02.670 --> 00:04:03.870
- Mm-hmm.
- And we'll grab other options

00:04:03.870 --> 00:04:05.970
so it's not just focused here.
- Mm-hmm.

00:04:05.970 --> 00:04:07.260
- The dress is amazing,

00:04:07.260 --> 00:04:10.020
but there's little perfecting
things that we need to do.

00:04:10.020 --> 00:04:12.390
But we have a few hours, basically,

00:04:12.390 --> 00:04:14.250
to figure it out before tomorrow.

00:04:14.250 --> 00:04:17.160
I think the only other thing
is I do wanna add a layer

00:04:17.160 --> 00:04:17.993
of this white mesh

00:04:17.993 --> 00:04:18.916
to the skirt as well.
- Yes, exactly.

00:04:18.916 --> 00:04:19.749
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

00:04:19.749 --> 00:04:20.730
- [Brett] Or do some beading around here

00:04:20.730 --> 00:04:22.470
to hide the seam a little.

00:04:22.470 --> 00:04:24.030
We're gonna take this off here.

00:04:24.030 --> 00:04:24.863
- [Robert] Yup.

00:04:24.863 --> 00:04:26.460
- We're gonna add a little bit
into the arms and the elbows

00:04:26.460 --> 00:04:28.410
and try to take the arms up a little bit.

00:04:28.410 --> 00:04:29.243
- [Robert] We should do that.

00:04:29.243 --> 00:04:31.290
I would do about like a centimeter.

00:04:31.290 --> 00:04:32.123
- Yeah.
- That's fine, just-

00:04:32.123 --> 00:04:32.956
- [Robert] That will be fine.

00:04:32.956 --> 00:04:34.770
- I am maybe a little
nervous about something.

00:04:34.770 --> 00:04:37.140
It's for a stylist and a creative,

00:04:37.140 --> 00:04:39.630
to not be able to be with
your artist on a carpet

00:04:39.630 --> 00:04:41.790
is always so hard because I force myself

00:04:41.790 --> 00:04:43.830
on every other carpet to
make sure things are good.

00:04:43.830 --> 00:04:45.660
But Met, you can't do that.

00:04:45.660 --> 00:04:48.090
I've tried and I've gotten yelled at.

00:04:48.090 --> 00:04:51.000
So this year, I am putting a lot of hope

00:04:51.000 --> 00:04:54.150
into our very handsome male handlers.

00:04:54.150 --> 00:04:57.450
I have a video for them to
show how to take the arms off.

00:04:57.450 --> 00:04:59.880
The veil, I've sent a voice
note really talking them through

00:04:59.880 --> 00:05:01.980
how to beautifully take the veil off,

00:05:01.980 --> 00:05:04.380
avoiding her face, avoiding the hair,

00:05:04.380 --> 00:05:05.670
to really try to make it look

00:05:05.670 --> 00:05:07.740
like it's almost this choreographed piece.

00:05:07.740 --> 00:05:09.840
- That's always gonna be
something I have to do.

00:05:09.840 --> 00:05:12.600
Until the second that
they're on the carpet

00:05:12.600 --> 00:05:14.670
and I no longer can reach them,

00:05:14.670 --> 00:05:15.930
there's always something you can do.

00:05:15.930 --> 00:05:17.940
Even a word of encouragement, you know?

00:05:17.940 --> 00:05:19.773
Sometimes you hold an artist and say like,

00:05:19.773 --> 00:05:21.270
"You look incredible.

00:05:21.270 --> 00:05:22.470
We got this."

00:05:22.470 --> 00:05:25.530
That will be always the last thing I do

00:05:25.530 --> 00:05:28.894
just to make sure that we're
enjoying this moment together.

00:05:28.894 --> 00:05:31.770
[mellow music]

00:05:31.770 --> 00:05:34.200
- Okay, "Vogue," wish me luck.

00:05:34.200 --> 00:05:35.109
Bye. See ya.

00:05:35.109 --> 00:05:36.192
Thank you, thank you.
- Making art.

00:05:36.192 --> 00:05:37.525
- Thank you, thank you.

00:05:37.525 --> 00:05:38.358
- No, thank you, baby.
- Oh.

00:05:38.358 --> 00:05:39.784
- Yeah, thank you.
- They see us, right,

00:05:39.784 --> 00:05:40.617
together, right?

00:05:40.617 --> 00:05:41.681
- All right, shall we-
- So we're gonna see

00:05:41.681 --> 00:05:43.641
that piece.
- We're having her.

